Paramedics say a 14-year-old was among the injured and been transported to hospital. JOHANNESBURG - Two people have been killed and two others seriously injured when the helicopter they were travelling in crashed in Heilbron in the Free State.At this stage, it s unclear where the aircraft took off from or where it was headed.Paramedics say a 14-year-old was among the injured and been transported to a hospital.ER24 spokesperson Werner Vermaak says, It s understood the helicopter crashed in the area and local emergency services were dispatched to the scene. A 14 year old and a 49 year old were found outside the helicopter with serious injuries. There were rushed to a clinic where ER24 was later called to assist with stabilisation. Local authorities attended the crash site and will investigate. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)